ref_solution:
Looking at triangle $ABD$, we can calculate $AB$ through the Pythagorean Theorem. \begin{align*}
AB&=\sqrt{37^2-(19+16)^2}\\
&=\sqrt{37^2-35^2}\\
&=\sqrt{(37+35)(37-35)}\\
&=\sqrt{72 \cdot 2}\\
&=\sqrt{36 \cdot 4}=6 \cdot 2=12\end{align*} Using Pythagorean theorem again to find $BC$, we get \begin{align*}
BC&=\sqrt{12^2+16^2}\\
&=\sqrt{4^2(3^2+4^2)}\\
&=4\sqrt{9+16}\\
&=4\sqrt{25}=4 \cdot 5=\boxed{20} \text{ units}.\end{align*}

